rComments: Gwen is one of the most gifted professor you will ever meet..she will brightened your worst day, and bring a smile to your face..god bless you Gwen..

Her class is great if native latin american history interests you, or if you have an open mind. I just want to add i have never met a professor, let alone teacher/counselor as helpful and caring as her, she really went out of her way in a situation where many profs would have been condescending. THANK YOU AGAIN FOR CARING PROF. RICE! :)

Gwen is an extremely knowledgable and intelligent woman. She knows her stuff! She has lived/lives all over the world and she is still young. Extremely kind and helpful, but she has high expectations - she forces everyone to challenge themselves, which can be a good or a bad thing, depending on how you look at it.

She's nice, funny, and really passionate about what she's teaching. The one critique I have is that her lectures tend to jump from one thing to the next and don't really capture the point they were set out to make. Nevertheless, I really enjoy her course.

She's okay, but she really loves her pictures. She's very interested in her subject material. Knowledgeable too. You can learn a lot from her class if you're interested in it. She dresses like a peasant at times though...
Simply wonderful. Gwen is enthusiastic and captivating and has an awesome sense of humour to boot. I would take absolutely any class that she teaches.
